 historical significance. Completed in 1938, the terminal building designed by architects Dag Englund and Vera Rosendahl is considered a prime example of functionalist architecture. \nIn 2016, the state withdrew its support for the light aircraft airport. Once state airports operator Finavia halted operations at the airfield, the Malmi Airfield Association stepped in to maintain the facility, which is an important site for pilot training. \nThe City of Helsinki has zoned the area for residential development for 25,000 residents. If this scale of housing development were to be implemented, the airfield would not be able to continue in operation. \nOther efforts to preserve the airfield included declaring it a site of historical and cultural significance. On 16 March 2016, Europe's leading cultural heritage organisation Europa Nostra selected Malmi Airport as one of the seven most endangered cultural heritage sites in Europe. Sources", "highlightText": "", "highlightTitle": "", "language": "english", "external_links": [], "entities": {"persons": [{"name": "juha sipil\u00e4", "sentiment": "none"}, {"name": "paula risikko", "sentiment": "none"}, {"name": "derrick frilund", "sentiment": "none"}, {"name": "lex malmi", "sentiment": "none"}], "organizations": [{"name": "parliament", "sentiment": "negative"}, {"name": "parliament\u2019s constitutional law committee", "sentiment": "none"}], "locations": [{"name": "malmi", "sentiment": "none"}, {"name": "malmi airport", "sentiment": "none"}, {"name": "helsinki", "sentiment": "none"}]}, "rating": null, "crawled": "2018-03-24T00:12:29.015+03:00"}], "totalResults": 11, "moreResultsAvailable": 1, "next": "/filterWebContent?token=e0e8b2b9-80ce-4cdc-bde9-b730ada6c3f9&format=json&ts=1521745982360&q=language%3Aenglish+site_type%3Anews+thread.country%3AFI+location%3AHelsinki&sort=relevancy&from=10&size=10", "requestsLeft": 904, "extra": {"place": "Helsinki", "country": "FI", "lat": "60.16985569999999", "lng": "24.9383791"}}